trend_summary: Built-up footprint radiates steadily from the historic center, with new subdivisions and light-industrial parks infilling forests and replacing fields, especially south and northwest. Road widening and a fresh arterial loop accelerate sprawl. Vegetation remains dominant, yet cropland acreage shrinks each period.
notable_changes: Progressive expansion of housing estates in the north-west quadrant, linking isolated clusters into a continuous suburb.
Construction of a south-western industrial/commercial park with large white-roof buildings after mid-series.
New curving arterial bypass and upgraded junctions improve east-west connectivity, visible by final frame.
Conversion of southern croplands to mixed residential lots and small commercial strips.
Patchy woodland regrowth over a former extraction site in the eastern interior.
